This feature allowed you to be a REAL pack. Having scouts, warriors, omegas, and more! Things i wish this game could improve on. 1: Controls. Sometimes they're a bit wonky but that doesn't make the game unplayable! 2: Pups. Normal wolf litters have about 1-4 pups. Why can we only have 1 pup at a time in this game? I just wish we could have more. Thanks for reading. I reccomend this game; its worth the dollar.

This game is really good! The model of the wolves are realistic,the amount of wolves are realistic,animals act realistically,but there's a few things I think need improvement. 1. The howls voice It would be awesome if you'd be able to choose how your howl sounded,like a low pitch,or a high pitch,or somewhere inbetween. 2. Some vocalization I think a whine,a bark,or something else would be cool! Also,some animals I think would need different vocals,but I forget which ones. 3. Movement The running,and walking,both look a bit unrealistic. Not all wolves lift their tail high when they walk,such as an omega,they keep their tail low and between their legs when they're respecting the alphas,their parents. Maybe when howling,the tail doesn't lift? And I'd like to see things such as a 'tail lift' emote,'ears pin' emote,'tuck tail' emote,and so on. 4. Litter sizes I think with pups,depending on if your wolf is healthy or unhealthy,the litters should vary in size like 0 is no pups because your wolf is too ill,1 for you're unhealthy,but had one pup,2 for eh,you were healthy enough for two,3 for you're in good shape,and 4 for you're all healthy,and had four beautiful pups! 5. Realistically defending and sizing a territory,and actually defending your pups I think it would be cool to be able to make a size to your territory,and have to mark it often,scare away lone wolves and rival packs,and so on. When I got the game and finally had puppers with Abyss and Bone,I was really hoping you can defend your pups from bears and foxes.. 6. More animals,and have different animals in both areas I think a few more animals like Coyotes (for puppers?),dogs,elk,cattle,and humans would be cool! And maybe you can have moose in both areas? I don't think I've seen a moose in the forests. 7. Bigger groups of animals and different animals are more difficult based on reality,and GENDERS for animals like deer I think having a bit more animals in groups of elk would be cool. Maybe have some females,a male,and some babies running around. I also think,as a bonus for the babies,the mother will try and protect the baby from the wolf(or wolves). A different difficulty for animals. Bunnies and other small animals are easy to kill,wolves are an even fight with you,elk are tough to kill on your own,moose,bears,and other large animals are very tough to kill,and require a good sized pack to kill. 8. Personality for NPCs I'd love to see your mate and other wolves have personality,such as bold,confident, courageous,shy,and aggressive. 9. Courting and groups of dispersal wolves It would be nice to have to win over a dispersal with sniffs,chin rests,tail wags,grins,play bows,and other friendly behavior to win over a female/male wolf to join you. It would also be interesting to see groups of dispersals,of the opposite gender of your wolf,come around you,and you can pick which wolf you want to have as a mate. I hope some of these get added into the game,if not we gucci. Anyways,I hope you have a great day! Yes,I know it was a pain reading this LOONG story book sized thing,but you really should consider some of these! It can attract more attention to your game,and make you more money!

The graphics are good, it's fun to hunt, there's a nice variety of animals and environments. But you have to get past a lot of broken or bad stuff. The last unlockable skin, the husky one, is a terrible reward for reaching max level. Animals run into hillsides and disappear, leveling is very slow past level ten or so so there are a lot of levelups where you don't get anything at all, and pack members (especially grown pups) lag far behind your original wolf in level so you have to spend even more time leveling them or they're useless in fights. Attacking cancels out running, which is annoying, unrealistic, and artificially makes hunting harder, and the energy meter goes down whenever you have running toggled, even if you're standing still.

Needs a compass. Amazing graphics improvement, the wolf looks just like a wolf and not a dog, and great additions with stat points and buffs. I'm eagerly awaiting leveling up and exploring the gigantic environment, which has pretty realistic sounds. The fact that you can tint the wolf is very nice, I just wish that there was a deep red, haha. The menu layout is concise. Being able to eat multiple times from large carcasses is a wonderful new trait. Since it's so hard to hunt prey, they shouldn't be able to run in water when the wolf is forced to swim and slow down. I can't corner them, either, because they run through walls. Also, since wolves are omnivores, they should be able to eat some plants, roots and fruits when prey is scarse. Edit: I did find a glitch where there are several white seams that stretch across the ground. I somehow found myself swimming in water when I entered the snowy tundra the first time. The lake's position on the mini-map does not correspond with its position in the wolf world. Can you add a sit or lie down button? Moonlight and shadows and phases for next sim?

Day 2: I came alive again and decided to hunt. Saw a deer and decided to give chase. Chased for a couple minutes until the deer became Jesus and ran across water. Another wolf saw I was tired and fought me. I died. Day 3: Chased a lamb. Lamb became Jesus. 10/10 would be such bad wolves that prey become Jesus.

I found out that to add more members to a pack. First thing first you can only add 1 at a time per every 10 level up. Level 5 you can bond. Level 15 you can have a pup. Level 25 you can finally bond with another wolf. And etc. So basically it will take forever to get a huge pack.  I think this should be more clear because it is not easy to level up. My suggestions is to delete and add new members each time you meet a stronger wolf.
